There it goes.

02:51.296 --> 02:53.765
Whoo! Whoo!

03:00.931 --> 03:03.730
Yes. Timing's still off 'bout two degrees.

03:04.351 --> 03:07.190
Looked fine to me. What you think?

03:07.270 --> 03:08.817
I think we won.

03:12.818 --> 03:16.322
That's fine right there. Now, come on.
Come on, now. Come on.

03:16.405 --> 03:18.282
Now that's a fast car you fellas got.

03:18.365 --> 03:21.118
And it's mighty fine of you
to let us boys race with y'all.

03:27.165 --> 03:28.587
Whoo!

04:00.365 --> 04:01.453
Get your hands out there, come on.

04:01.533 --> 04:03.001
Come on, Garnet, come on.

04:03.118 --> 04:05.837
Get ready to dance with old Virgil.
Come on.

04:33.648 --> 04:35.195
Damn, Richard. Slow down.

04:43.909 --> 04:46.708
- All right now.
- Where you going?

05:08.767 --> 05:11.520
What you think? Do you like it?

05:15.398 --> 05:16.570
Like what?

05:18.068 --> 05:19.911
This spot. Right here.

05:24.449 --> 05:25.662
This field?

05:25.742 --> 05:26.914
Yeah.

05:29.996 --> 05:33.250
This field not a half a mile from my house
I've been knowing all my life?

05:33.708 --> 05:36.507
Yeah, yeah.

05:42.175 --> 05:44.928
Yes. I like it.

05:52.310 --> 05:55.189
I'm gonna put the kitchen back.
Right back here.

05:55.272 --> 05:56.945
Richard, stop this!

05:57.858 --> 05:59.781
I don't know what you're saying.

06:06.241 --> 06:07.709
I bought it.

06:09.995 --> 06:11.622
This whole acre.

06:17.460 --> 06:19.462
I'm gonna build you a house.

06:20.839 --> 06:22.136
Right here.

06:26.136 --> 06:27.854
Our house.

06:42.027 --> 06:44.325
Mildred?

06:46.990 --> 06:48.333
Yes?

06:52.662 --> 06:54.005
Would you marry me?

07:12.223 --> 07:14.100
Garnet, come.

07:16.895 --> 07:19.648
He said he'd bought the whole acre for me.

07:21.316 --> 07:23.114
And then he asked me to marry him.

07:23.360 --> 07:25.203
- No he didn't!
- Yes.

07:25.362 --> 07:27.205
- Right out in the field?
- Uh-huh.

07:27.364 --> 07:30.208
Oh, Lord, that man might be crazy.

07:31.451 --> 07:33.124
Well, when you gonna do it?

07:33.578 --> 07:35.046
He didn't say.

07:36.373 --> 07:37.499
Soon, though.

07:38.541 --> 07:40.794
Before the baby comes.

07:44.339 --> 07:46.341
He gonna take my sister from me?

07:47.467 --> 07:48.684
No.

07:50.220 --> 07:52.222
We'll be right down the road.

08:17.580 --> 08:19.002
Everything looks fine.

08:20.917 --> 08:24.342
- Thank you, Miss Lola. We'll see you soon.
- We'll be here.

08:26.673 --> 08:27.674
Hey, now.

08:29.634 --> 08:31.853
- Hey, Momma.
- They're out back.

08:43.773 --> 08:45.946
- How we doing?
- Hmm.

08:46.443 --> 08:49.947
Get that board and get up under there.
See if you can get that collector loose.

09:12.635 --> 09:15.013
So I'm gonna take Mildred
up to D.C. to get married.

09:18.767 --> 09:20.314
So, you sure about that?

09:21.895 --> 09:23.488
Yeah.

09:30.612 --> 09:32.330
And you need a witness?

09:32.989 --> 09:34.160
No.

09:34.240 --> 09:36.743
I'm gonna ask her dad
to come up there with us.

09:39.996 --> 09:42.293
Rich is gonna take Mildred
up to D.C. to get married.

09:42.373 --> 09:44.046
String Bean?

09:44.709 --> 09:48.009
Don't make no damn sense.
Now, you'd be fine living in the house.

09:48.296 --> 09:50.799
No wife, just fine.
You don't need no wife.

09:50.882 --> 09:53.260
Well, now, she gonna be your girl.
Why people wanna get married?

09:53.343 --> 09:54.469
Don't make no sense, man.

10:01.184 --> 10:03.186
You think they'll see us today?

10:04.354 --> 10:06.231
Yeah. I called up there.

10:08.274 --> 10:10.402
Seem like a long drive to me.

10:13.863 --> 10:15.331
Thanks for coming, Jake.

10:20.411 --> 10:22.163
Daddy, what's the city like?

10:25.500 --> 10:27.047
It's fine.

10:39.222 --> 10:43.147
Marriage is an institution
of the highest importance.

10:43.685 --> 10:46.313
And it's made honorable
by faithful couples

10:46.396 --> 10:49.400
who are committed to each other for life.

10:49.774 --> 10:51.117
Do you have the ring?

10:58.700 --> 11:03.080
By the power vested in me
by the District of Columbia,

11:03.496 --> 11:06.591
I now pronounce you husband and wife.

11:13.256 --> 11:14.599
I may not forgive him.

11:16.467 --> 11:17.806
Come on, now.

11:17.886 --> 11:19.724
You lucky if I forgive you.

11:19.804 --> 11:23.058
No reason to go all the way up there
for this and not take us.

11:23.683 --> 11:25.271
We took Daddy.

11:25.351 --> 11:27.649
Like that means a thing.

11:28.396 --> 11:31.445
Richard said there would be less
red tape in Washington. That's all.

11:33.776 --> 11:37.451
You can stop looking at it,
String Bean, you know it's purdy.

12:00.803 --> 12:02.100
I'm turning in.

12:02.972 --> 12:05.851
What you think 'bout
a bedroom in the back?

12:07.977 --> 12:09.399
I'll like it however you make it.

12:17.987 --> 12:19.330
I'll be in there soon.

12:19.948 --> 12:21.200
Mmm-hmm.

13:09.622 --> 13:10.874
I thought something like this.

13:42.071 --> 13:43.414
Hey, Momma.

13:46.659 --> 13:49.082
Sheriff's Deputy came by looking for you.

13:52.081 --> 13:53.333
What did he want?

13:54.250 --> 13:55.752
Wanted to find you.

13:59.297 --> 14:00.719
Hmm.

14:01.215 --> 14:03.263
Did you tell him where I was?

14:03.926 --> 14:05.769
I didn't have nothing to tell him.

14:30.620 --> 14:32.668
Like me raising a barn, but, you know...

14:34.123 --> 14:37.377
Thinking the kind of fuel in that car,
that was different.

14:38.503 --> 14:41.882
- That car was great.
- Applesauce good.

14:41.964 --> 14:43.682
But, you know...

14:45.301 --> 14:47.303
What you like, Rich, Ford or Chevy?

14:47.678 --> 14:49.646
Eh, don't make much difference.

14:49.764 --> 14:51.016
But which one faster?

14:52.100 --> 14:53.352
That depend on who built it.

14:53.434 --> 14:54.560
That's what I said.

14:56.145 --> 14:57.358
How much money you win with that car?

14:57.438 --> 14:59.402
Boy, why you're asking
him about his money?

14:59.482 --> 15:01.155
He doesn't have to answer me.

15:02.110 --> 15:03.612
How many races you won, Rich?

15:03.694 --> 15:04.695
Oh.

15:05.780 --> 15:07.373
Uh...

15:14.330 --> 15:15.832
A lot.

15:17.333 --> 15:19.836
You need my hand, you need
my hand, too? Count on this one.

15:22.922 --> 15:24.265
I didn't think he was gonna stop.

15:26.968 --> 15:28.094
I wanna know, you know?

15:28.177 --> 15:29.394
Ask that question...

16:40.291 --> 16:41.712
In here!

16:41.792 --> 16:43.920
What you doing in that bed, boy?

16:44.670 --> 16:47.264
- Richard?
- What're you doing in bed with that woman?

16:48.841 --> 16:50.218
I'm his wife.

16:56.974 --> 16:58.601
That's no good here.

16:59.435 --> 17:00.857
Get your pants on, boy.

17:02.230 --> 17:03.777
You get out of that bed.

17:06.025 --> 17:07.617
Get out of that bed!

17:11.571 --> 17:12.789
All right.

17:14.867 --> 17:16.414
Come on.

17:34.178 --> 17:35.304
All right.

17:50.778 --> 17:52.530
She goes in there.

17:54.699 --> 17:56.076
It's all right.

17:58.578 --> 17:59.665
- Come on!
- It's okay.

17:59.745 --> 18:01.213
It's okay.

18:50.338 --> 18:51.590
Richard Loving?

18:51.672 --> 18:52.673
Yeah.

18:53.382 --> 18:54.599
You made bail.

18:59.805 --> 19:00.806
Bean?

19:01.432 --> 19:02.558
Bean?

19:03.643 --> 19:04.644
Richard?

19:08.856 --> 19:09.857
Go on down.

19:10.149 --> 19:11.988
- What about her?
- Just you.

19:12.068 --> 19:14.321
What do you mean? Wait, wait. Wait!

19:15.154 --> 19:16.747
Don't pull me again.

19:18.741 --> 19:20.493
- Come on now.
- That's not right.

19:22.036 --> 19:23.037
Bean.

19:23.996 --> 19:25.339
Richard?

19:26.999 --> 19:29.878
- It ain't right now!
- Come on!

19:29.960 --> 19:31.678
It ain't right!

19:56.445 --> 19:58.288
Sign at the bottom.

20:00.408 --> 20:01.876
What about my wife?

20:02.159 --> 20:04.412
You'll have to talk to the Judge
about that on Monday.

20:06.163 --> 20:07.415
Monday?

20:35.234 --> 20:37.032
That's good.

20:37.194 --> 20:39.241
Okay. Just rest. Just rest.

20:39.321 --> 20:40.538
Richard!

20:42.491 --> 20:43.954
- Richard!
- Yeah?

20:44.034 --> 20:46.207
Bring me that fresh water
and take this one out.

20:46.287 --> 20:47.504
Okay.

20:49.081 --> 20:50.207
Bear down.

20:51.000 --> 20:52.343
Bear down.

20:54.754 --> 20:56.677
- Here, Mom.
- Leave that down.

20:57.339 --> 20:58.552
Good. Good.

20:58.632 --> 21:00.134
Wait. Wait.

21:33.375 --> 21:34.843
What you gonna do?

21:41.425 --> 21:43.302
How did they know to come get us?

21:45.721 --> 21:47.394
Somebody talked.

22:55.124 --> 22:57.297
Hey!

22:57.835 --> 22:58.836
Hey!

23:02.798 --> 23:06.098
We told you to come back
on Monday and talk to the Judge.

23:06.218 --> 23:07.891
I ain't gonna let her
stay there till Monday.

23:09.096 --> 23:11.098
- It's not right.
- Talk to the Judge.

23:11.765 --> 23:13.312
You're not allowed to bail her out.

23:15.352 --> 23:17.696
- I'll get a lawyer.
- You can.

23:32.953 --> 23:34.500
Hey, boy.

23:38.000 --> 23:39.001
Come on.

23:58.187 --> 23:59.188
Sit down.

24:11.575 --> 24:13.828
You back here trying to bail her out?

24:18.624 --> 24:21.127
You know they aren't gonna
let her out to you?

24:22.836 --> 24:25.134
You best send some of
her people up here to get her,

24:25.214 --> 24:27.057
because they won't let her out to you.

24:29.843 --> 24:32.346
- But, she's pregnant.
- Shut your mouth about that.

24:32.429 --> 24:35.308
I'll throw your ass back in there
for that. You know better.

24:38.852 --> 24:39.853
It's just not...

24:40.562 --> 24:41.779
What's that?

24:45.526 --> 24:47.449
You do know better, don't you?

24:50.406 --> 24:51.578
Nah, maybe you don't.

24:54.451 --> 24:56.419
Your daddy worked for a nigger, didn't he?

24:59.623 --> 25:00.920
Running timber?

25:04.753 --> 25:06.300
I'm sorry for you.

25:06.380 --> 25:08.007
No, I really am.

25:08.090 --> 25:10.763
All you over there in Central Point
don't know up from down.

25:10.843 --> 25:12.431
All mixed up.

25:12.511 --> 25:13.683
Part Cherokee,

25:14.596 --> 25:16.143
Rappahannock,

25:16.223 --> 25:18.021
part niggra, part white.

25:19.685 --> 25:21.437
Blood don't know what it wants to be.

25:24.773 --> 25:26.992
You just got born in
the wrong place, is all.

25:30.487 --> 25:32.285
I see you got to thinking it was fine.

25:35.367 --> 25:37.369
You might think people
around here wouldn't care.

25:41.290 --> 25:43.167
Hell, maybe they wouldn't,
if your dumb country ass

25:43.250 --> 25:45.047
hadn't gone off
and married her, but not me.

25:45.127 --> 25:46.128
You hear me?

25:50.090 --> 25:51.262
That's God's law.

25:52.426 --> 25:55.145
He made a sparrow a sparrow
and a robin a robin.

25:55.971 --> 25:57.439
They're different for a reason.

26:04.021 --> 26:05.022
No.

26:09.151 --> 26:10.152
No.

26:14.782 --> 26:15.783
You go on now.

26:16.992 --> 26:17.993
Get on home.

26:22.289 --> 26:24.462
Send some of her people
up here on Monday to get her.

26:25.834 --> 26:27.928
I see you trying to bail her out
again, I'll arrest you.

27:45.581 --> 27:47.504
I should put you in with her tonight.

28:07.186 --> 28:08.779
Your daddy posted your bail.

28:36.840 --> 28:38.387
It's all right, Bean.

28:41.970 --> 28:43.768
It's all right.

29:21.176 --> 29:22.268
Where's Richard?

29:23.011 --> 29:24.513
He moved his things out.

29:27.266 --> 29:30.936
Said they'd arrest y'all again,
if they catch him here with you.

29:44.533 --> 29:46.285
Now, come on. Come on here.

29:46.368 --> 29:47.665
Come on.

30:38.545 --> 30:39.637
Bean?

30:41.256 --> 30:43.600
Hey. It's okay.

30:44.843 --> 30:45.969
Oh, I got you.

30:54.019 --> 30:55.691
You okay?

30:55.771 --> 30:57.444
They hurt you?

30:58.023 --> 30:59.024
No.

31:02.736 --> 31:04.113
I'm just scared.

31:07.532 --> 31:09.205
They said I couldn't see you.

31:09.743 --> 31:10.744
I know.

31:14.956 --> 31:16.503
What are we gonna do?

31:16.583 --> 31:17.800
I got a lawyer.

31:19.127 --> 31:21.471
They say he's the best in the county.

31:22.964 --> 31:24.807
He gonna get it all straightened out.

31:27.928 --> 31:29.555
- I don't know.
- It's fine.

31:29.638 --> 31:34.067
All we gotta do is just keep
to ourselves for a while.

31:35.227 --> 31:36.649
And this will blow over.

31:38.605 --> 31:39.606
Yeah?

31:57.124 --> 31:58.171
I better go.

32:12.764 --> 32:14.016
Better go.

32:45.714 --> 32:47.387
We'll walk over there in a minute.

32:48.133 --> 32:49.971
But I met with the Judge this morning,

32:50.051 --> 32:52.679
and I worked out a deal
I think is pretty fair.

32:53.388 --> 32:54.810
Judge Bazile is a friend.

32:55.599 --> 32:59.069
But he is not a fan
of your particular situation.

32:59.978 --> 33:01.901
If you all plead guilty,

33:02.481 --> 33:05.360
the Judge is willing
to suspend any prison time.

33:10.280 --> 33:11.281
Hmm.

33:15.660 --> 33:16.661
We'll do it.

33:17.245 --> 33:21.082
Now, in exchange for suspending
the jail time, you and your wife,

33:21.875 --> 33:24.924
unless you decide to
dissolve the marriage,

33:26.087 --> 33:27.760
will be forced to leave the state.

33:31.218 --> 33:32.470
Leave the state?

33:33.637 --> 33:35.264
What does that mean?

33:35.347 --> 33:36.974
It's exactly what it sounds like.

33:37.766 --> 33:41.189
You two are not allowed to be
in the state at the same time,

33:41.269 --> 33:43.363
and certainly, aren't allowed
to be here together.

33:44.356 --> 33:46.450
For how long? How long will that last?

33:49.569 --> 33:50.570
Twenty-five years.

33:55.158 --> 33:56.580
That can't be right.

33:56.701 --> 33:58.829
Look, you got a year
in state penitentiary,

33:58.912 --> 34:01.710
which, I remind you, could have been
up to five years at the maximum,

34:01.790 --> 34:05.460
you got a year in prison on one hand,
and leaving the state on the other.

34:06.795 --> 34:08.138
That's an easy choice.

34:23.061 --> 34:27.485
Try not to talk unless he directly
asks you a question, which he won't.

34:27.774 --> 34:30.447
Just like we talked about,
he'll ask what you plead,

34:30.527 --> 34:32.996
you say guilty, and this will be
over quick enough.

34:36.408 --> 34:38.034
"...the said Richard Perry Loving,

34:38.326 --> 34:42.248
"being a white person,
and the said Mildred Dolores Jeter,

34:42.330 --> 34:46.087
"being a colored person,
did unlawfully and feloniously,

34:46.167 --> 34:49.920
"go out of the state of Virginia,
for the purpose of being married

34:50.005 --> 34:54.217
"in the District of Columbia,
on June 2nd, 1958,

34:54.759 --> 34:56.598
"and afterwards returned to,

34:56.678 --> 34:59.392
"and resided in the County of Caroline,

34:59.472 --> 35:03.438
"State of Virginia,
cohabitating as man and wife,

35:03.518 --> 35:06.488
"against the peace and dignity
of the Commonwealth."

35:08.690 --> 35:09.862
How do you plead?

35:14.154 --> 35:15.155
Guilty.

35:18.283 --> 35:19.284
Guilty.

35:20.035 --> 35:22.458
The court does accept the plea of guilty,

35:23.163 --> 35:27.384
and fixed the punishment
of both accused at one year in jail.

35:29.711 --> 35:34.675
The court does suspend said sentence
for the period of 25 years,

35:34.758 --> 35:36.721
upon the provision that both the accused

35:36.801 --> 35:39.395
leave Caroline County
and the State of Virginia at once.

35:40.055 --> 35:42.808
And do not return together
at the same time

35:42.891 --> 35:46.733
to said county and state
for a period of 25 years.

35:48.938 --> 35:50.485
Do either of you have anything to say?

35:52.567 --> 35:53.568
No, sir.

35:55.403 --> 35:56.404
No, sir.

35:57.322 --> 35:59.825
You are released from custody.
Settle your court costs with clerk.

36:01.201 --> 36:02.418
Thank you, Your Honor.

36:05.080 --> 36:07.043
It's 36 dollars

36:07.123 --> 36:09.342
and 29 cents apiece.

36:25.392 --> 36:28.271
That's a number in Washington
for Nancy's brother Alex.

36:29.562 --> 36:31.610
His wife Laura's there most days.

36:34.609 --> 36:36.282
If you need to get us, just call.

36:36.945 --> 36:37.946
Okay.

36:48.081 --> 36:49.082
Daddy?

36:53.128 --> 36:54.129
You okay?

37:06.015 --> 37:08.484
You knew what you
was doing taking her up there!

37:09.728 --> 37:11.321
You had no right for that!

37:28.079 --> 37:29.080
Bean?

40:13.703 --> 40:14.704
How you all doing?

40:15.038 --> 40:16.335
We're fine.

40:17.165 --> 40:18.417
Thank you for taking us.

40:19.167 --> 40:20.544
We've got plenty of room.

40:21.294 --> 40:22.921
- You remember Richard?
- Yes.

40:23.922 --> 40:24.968
Thank you.

40:25.048 --> 40:26.470
No. Glad to have you.

40:27.550 --> 40:29.223
Come on in. Let me show you the house.

40:47.487 --> 40:50.115
Yeah, they live, like, what,
two blocks over there, right?

40:50.198 --> 40:51.450
I know them.

41:34.409 --> 41:35.410
Okay.

41:53.594 --> 41:55.062
I'll be back by dinner.

