Nothing.

43:59.137 --> 44:00.138
Bean.

44:04.100 --> 44:05.101
It's just...

44:10.356 --> 44:13.568
I always thought your mother
would be the woman to deliver the baby.

44:23.369 --> 44:24.370
Damn it.

44:32.670 --> 44:33.717
Okay.

44:39.468 --> 44:40.515
Okay.

48:07.802 --> 48:09.554
Hey, Momma.

48:09.637 --> 48:11.605
Put some wood in the stove.

48:32.118 --> 48:33.620
Thank you for doing this.

48:35.955 --> 48:37.002
All right.

48:47.383 --> 48:49.306
All right, String Bean, it's on you now.

48:53.055 --> 48:54.898
- Yes, it is.
- Drink this.

49:11.657 --> 49:12.658
Rich!

49:15.035 --> 49:16.036
Rich!

49:20.875 --> 49:22.969
Her water broke.

49:29.216 --> 49:31.435
Okay. Take a breath. Take a breath.

49:35.097 --> 49:36.565
Breathe.

49:39.310 --> 49:40.778
Okay. Bear down.

49:41.312 --> 49:42.564
Bear down hard.

50:04.710 --> 50:05.962
Thank you, Momma.

50:10.466 --> 50:12.764
You never should have married that girl.

50:17.515 --> 50:19.188
Well, I thought you liked her.

50:20.684 --> 50:22.106
I like a lot of people.

50:23.270 --> 50:26.023
That doesn't mean you should have
gone and done what you did.

50:27.650 --> 50:29.072
You knew better.

50:46.669 --> 50:48.137
Sidney.

50:49.463 --> 50:50.931
Hi, Sidney.

50:55.135 --> 50:56.478
Sidney.

51:42.266 --> 51:43.609
Call the lawyer.

52:19.053 --> 52:20.726
Tell that woman to come out here.

52:26.894 --> 52:28.066
She ain't here.

52:30.397 --> 52:31.610
She left.

52:31.690 --> 52:34.284
Boy, I will split your
head into white meat,

52:35.944 --> 52:38.072
and go arrest every soul in that house.

52:43.118 --> 52:44.665
I won't ask you again.

53:05.849 --> 53:06.850
No.

54:18.046 --> 54:19.343
You are in luck.

54:20.507 --> 54:22.180
The Judge is in today.

54:23.927 --> 54:25.304
You'll go straight there.

54:31.268 --> 54:35.943
For violation of your parole,
you are ordered to post a $200 bond,

54:36.982 --> 54:38.696
and appear before this court...

54:38.776 --> 54:39.902
In the next...

54:47.701 --> 54:48.748
Yes, Frank?

54:50.037 --> 54:53.041
We ask for leniency.

54:53.957 --> 54:57.211
I incorrectly told the Lovings
it was fine for them to return home

54:57.294 --> 54:58.465
for the birth of their child.

54:58.545 --> 55:01.970
It... It was my mistake.

55:08.764 --> 55:10.311
Your Honor, I think...

55:22.402 --> 55:23.528
Fine.

55:45.050 --> 55:46.222
Thank you.

55:49.304 --> 55:50.681
Don't come back here again.

55:52.057 --> 55:53.559
You do and you go to prison.

55:54.977 --> 55:56.524
This doesn't happen a second time.

57:23.357 --> 57:26.031
Sidney, Donald, come on down.

57:27.778 --> 57:28.950
Hey!

57:31.073 --> 57:32.165
Okay.

57:33.325 --> 57:35.043
Okay.

57:40.707 --> 57:42.050
Come on in.

57:47.631 --> 57:49.008
You go.

57:49.091 --> 57:50.304
Hi, pretty girl.

57:53.512 --> 57:56.436
Your cousin, Gerald and Davis, are fine,

57:56.556 --> 57:59.396
and Sue and Terry send their love.

57:59.476 --> 58:01.695
They just had a little girl, too.

58:02.354 --> 58:04.818
- Really?
- Their second.

58:04.898 --> 58:05.899
Hmm.

58:07.484 --> 58:09.407
Sidney, don't jump in the house.

58:12.072 --> 58:13.494
They're big.

58:15.742 --> 58:17.289
Yes.

58:19.329 --> 58:20.876
I hate it for them.

58:22.916 --> 58:23.917
It's like they're caged.

58:27.129 --> 58:29.223
Not even any grass for them to run in.

58:32.217 --> 58:33.343
And Daddy?

58:33.927 --> 58:37.227
He's fine. Stays up in that
chair more than in the field.

58:37.931 --> 58:40.228
I told Momma if he don't start
getting some work done,

58:40.308 --> 58:42.856
Mr. Banks liable to find
someone else for it.

58:42.936 --> 58:45.651
Clay said he'd have to stay
with me until after the party.

59:13.508 --> 59:17.388
- Good. How are you doing?
- Where is that piece?

59:18.805 --> 59:20.307
How was your sister?

59:21.308 --> 59:23.527
- I need one piece.
- She's fine.

59:29.941 --> 59:33.240
- I almost have it.
- Yeah? You wanna show me?

59:33.320 --> 59:36.368
The long awaited march
for jobs and freedom

59:36.448 --> 59:38.450
on Washington D.C., has started

59:38.533 --> 59:42.457
and it's about half of the
100, 000 estimated crowd

59:42.537 --> 59:46.086
headed off down Constitution Avenue
toward the Lincoln Memorial

59:46.166 --> 59:48.255
which is where we're seated now.

59:48.335 --> 59:50.713
It is here that the climax of the march...

59:50.796 --> 59:53.760
You boys stop that wrestling.

59:53.840 --> 59:55.934
Come and help Miss Laura
with her groceries.

59:56.384 --> 59:59.684
...coming in around the plaza
surrounding Lincoln Memorial.

01:00:01.181 --> 01:00:03.058
They say over 100,000 people are there.

01:00:03.517 --> 01:00:07.567
...is standing by along the parade
route at 17th and Constitution.

01:00:07.729 --> 01:00:08.855
Can you imagine?

01:00:10.941 --> 01:00:13.613
Might as well be half way
around the world.

01:00:13.693 --> 01:00:15.070
What?

01:00:16.363 --> 01:00:17.535
Nothing.

01:00:21.034 --> 01:00:22.372
You know what you need to do?

01:00:22.452 --> 01:00:23.578
What?

01:00:24.746 --> 01:00:26.123
You need to write Bobby Kennedy.

01:00:27.415 --> 01:00:28.712
I'm serious.

01:00:29.543 --> 01:00:31.420
I mean, that's what they up there for.

01:00:31.503 --> 01:00:33.717
All this talk of civil rights.

01:00:33.797 --> 01:00:35.594
You need to get you some civil rights.

01:00:35.674 --> 01:00:37.971
...engaged in demonstrations before.

01:00:38.051 --> 01:00:40.891
In the background, you can hear
some of the young people shouting.

01:00:42.889 --> 01:00:44.687
"Freedom, freedom now."

01:01:51.333 --> 01:01:52.334
Mmm.

01:01:58.298 --> 01:02:00.175
- They in bed?
- Mmm-hmm.

01:02:01.968 --> 01:02:03.345
I'm sorry I missed them.

01:02:04.971 --> 01:02:06.768
They ask for me?

01:02:06.848 --> 01:02:08.145
Peggy did,

01:02:09.100 --> 01:02:10.443
but she went down fine.

01:02:13.980 --> 01:02:15.402
Will you get Saturday off?

01:02:18.068 --> 01:02:19.365
I hope so.

01:02:37.879 --> 01:02:39.593
Sidney, get up
and strip those sheets for me.

01:02:39.673 --> 01:02:42.347
My turn, my turn, my turn! My turn.

01:02:42.717 --> 01:02:45.182
Don, make sure your sister gets a turn.

01:02:45.262 --> 01:02:47.264
My turn, my turn, my turn.

01:02:51.810 --> 01:02:53.062
Byrd residence.

01:02:53.979 --> 01:02:56.357
Hello, I'm calling to speak
to Mildred Loving.

01:03:01.194 --> 01:03:02.946
This is she.

01:03:03.029 --> 01:03:05.452
Hello, Mrs. Loving,
my name is Bernard Cohen,

01:03:05.532 --> 01:03:08.330
I'm the lawyer that was referred
to you by the ACLU.

01:03:08.410 --> 01:03:10.412
Are you familiar?

01:03:10.495 --> 01:03:12.209
I'm sorry. No.

01:03:12.289 --> 01:03:15.543
You wrote a letter to Attorney
General Kennedy, is that right?

01:03:17.419 --> 01:03:18.757
Yes.

01:03:18.837 --> 01:03:21.301
He was not able to help you
with your particular case,

01:03:21.381 --> 01:03:24.134
and sent your letter
to the American Civil Liberties Union.

01:03:24.217 --> 01:03:27.015
The ACLU contacted me,
I'm a lawyer in Virginia,

01:03:27.095 --> 01:03:28.893
and we would like to
help you with your case.

01:03:31.850 --> 01:03:33.313
I see.

01:03:33.393 --> 01:03:36.818
- Momma! Momma!
- Don, baby, hush.

01:03:38.064 --> 01:03:41.364
Would it be possible for you
and your husband to meet with me?

01:03:45.947 --> 01:03:48.041
I would have to check with my husband.

01:03:49.659 --> 01:03:51.498
Okay. I'm based in Alexandria,

01:03:51.578 --> 01:03:54.457
but I have an office in D.C.
If that is a concern.

01:03:55.749 --> 01:03:59.589
Well, as I said in my letter,
we really can't afford a lawyer.

01:03:59.669 --> 01:04:02.673
No, ma'am.
The ACLU will take care of any fees.

01:04:09.137 --> 01:04:11.231
Mrs. Loving? Are you there?

01:04:14.351 --> 01:04:17.065
- Yes, we'll see you.
- Wonderful.

01:04:17.145 --> 01:04:20.193
I'll have my secretary
call you back to set up a time.

01:04:20.273 --> 01:04:22.275
Nice speaking with you, Mrs. Loving.

01:04:35.497 --> 01:04:36.749
Come here, baby.

01:04:39.376 --> 01:04:41.003
I got a call from a lawyer today.

01:04:43.963 --> 01:04:46.216
- A lawyer?
- Mmm-hmm.

01:04:46.299 --> 01:04:49.303
From the American Civil Liberties Union.

01:04:49.386 --> 01:04:51.229
Robert Kennedy told him to call us.

01:04:52.472 --> 01:04:54.190
Go help your sister brush her teeth.

01:04:56.851 --> 01:04:58.694
They wanna help with our case.

01:04:59.813 --> 01:05:02.191
Well, we can't afford a lawyer.

01:05:02.273 --> 01:05:03.695
He said they wouldn't charge us.

01:05:06.194 --> 01:05:08.867
I'm gonna go see him on Thursday.

01:05:08.947 --> 01:05:10.199
His name is Cohen.

01:05:33.721 --> 01:05:35.518
Hello.

01:05:35.598 --> 01:05:37.395
I'm Bernard Cohen. I'm in from Richmond.

01:05:37.475 --> 01:05:39.773
I talked to Jim about using
his office for a few hours.

01:05:39.853 --> 01:05:41.105
Yes, Mr. Cohen, do you know it?

01:05:41.187 --> 01:05:42.530
- Down the hall?
- Yes.

01:05:44.774 --> 01:05:46.401
My clients are Mr. and Mrs. Loving.

01:05:46.484 --> 01:05:47.822
Could you send them down when they arrive?

01:05:47.902 --> 01:05:49.028
Certainly.

01:06:29.861 --> 01:06:31.033
Come in.

01:06:34.574 --> 01:06:35.995
- Mrs. Loving.
- Hello.

01:06:36.075 --> 01:06:37.372
Please, have a seat.

01:06:38.203 --> 01:06:41.047
Bernard Cohen. It's a pleasure.

01:06:45.418 --> 01:06:46.761
Thank you for coming in today.

01:06:48.171 --> 01:06:52.303
So, as we discussed on the phone,
the ACLU would like to take on your case.

01:06:52.383 --> 01:06:55.306
I was actually a charter member
of the ACLU in Virginia,

01:06:55.386 --> 01:06:57.309
which is why they assigned me to you.

01:06:57.764 --> 01:07:01.109
The bottom line is,
we wanna get you all some relief.

01:07:03.436 --> 01:07:06.234
That's very generous. Thank you.

01:07:06.314 --> 01:07:10.069
Now, the first step is to appeal
the sentence in Caroline County.

01:07:10.235 --> 01:07:12.988
That will be our fastest
route to Federal Court.

01:07:13.071 --> 01:07:14.744
- The problem is...
- Federal Court?

01:07:15.949 --> 01:07:18.953
Yes, the goal is to try to get
the Federal Court to hear the case...

01:07:19.035 --> 01:07:21.834
Excuse me, I don't understand...
Federal Court.

01:07:23.164 --> 01:07:24.586
I see it as the best route...

01:07:24.666 --> 01:07:27.215
Can't you just go and
speak to Judge Bazile?

01:07:28.127 --> 01:07:29.970
I mean, we ain't hurting anybody.

01:07:30.338 --> 01:07:32.591
- I don't think that...
- Well, just talk to him.

01:07:32.674 --> 01:07:34.142
Just talk to him.

01:07:35.134 --> 01:07:37.978
Just tell him if he lets
us back in the state,

01:07:40.139 --> 01:07:41.516
we won't bother anybody.

01:07:47.480 --> 01:07:50.528
Look, I do not think that this case

01:07:50.608 --> 01:07:52.906
will be resolved in Judge Bazile's court,

01:07:52.986 --> 01:07:56.240
or probably any other court
in the state of Virginia.

01:07:56.322 --> 01:08:00.744
I believe this is a court battle that could
go all the way to the Supreme Court.

01:08:09.002 --> 01:08:10.254
We're listening.

01:08:14.382 --> 01:08:17.761
Our problem is that in order
to appeal the judgment of conviction,

01:08:17.844 --> 01:08:20.433
we would have needed to
do so within 60 days.

01:08:20.513 --> 01:08:23.937
Now, given that it's been five
years since that conviction,

01:08:24.017 --> 01:08:26.856
we have to find a way
to get it back into the courts.

01:08:26.935 --> 01:08:28.899
- Are you following?
- Mmm-hmm.

01:08:28.979 --> 01:08:30.527
Mmm-hmm.

01:08:30.607 --> 01:08:32.278
Now, I've given this some thought,

01:08:32.358 --> 01:08:36.238
and I have a somewhat unorthodox
idea on how to do this.

01:08:36.696 --> 01:08:40.662
My suggestion would be for the two
of you to return to Caroline County,

01:08:40.742 --> 01:08:45.292
get re-arrested, and then we will
have an avenue for our appeal.

01:08:50.417 --> 01:08:52.341
You want us to get arrested again?

01:08:53.504 --> 01:08:54.630
Yes. It's an idea.

01:08:54.714 --> 01:08:56.557
I, of course, will be
there to bail you out.

01:09:03.555 --> 01:09:05.103
We aren't gonna do that.

01:09:07.894 --> 01:09:09.020
Right...

01:09:11.272 --> 01:09:13.115
I can see how that was a mistake.

01:09:14.817 --> 01:09:16.033
I understand.

01:09:18.071 --> 01:09:22.036
Look, I need to do some more
thinking on this first issue, but,

01:09:22.116 --> 01:09:24.915
bottom line is we are gonna
get you all some help.

01:09:31.376 --> 01:09:32.627
We appreciate you.

01:09:34.379 --> 01:09:35.631
We really do.

01:09:38.716 --> 01:09:39.763
Yeah.

01:10:23.511 --> 01:10:25.639
If it gets us home, we'll take their help.

01:10:28.266 --> 01:10:31.564
Well, you get what you pay for.

01:10:47.618 --> 01:10:48.744
Get off the street!

01:11:08.514 --> 01:11:09.686
Lee, give him a hand!

01:11:19.984 --> 01:11:22.448
You gotta pull that concrete. Yeah.

01:11:22.528 --> 01:11:23.529
Pull more.

01:11:26.449 --> 01:11:28.201
- Whoo-hoo!
- I got it!

01:11:29.535 --> 01:11:30.536
Hey!

01:11:30.870 --> 01:11:32.338
Look out!

01:11:38.252 --> 01:11:39.253
Donald!

01:11:46.135 --> 01:11:47.387
Momma!

01:11:48.471 --> 01:11:49.518
Momma!

01:12:40.439 --> 01:12:42.362
- Mildred!
- Up here!

01:12:50.783 --> 01:12:51.830
What's going on?

01:12:52.702 --> 01:12:54.500
Donald got hit by a car today.

01:12:57.748 --> 01:12:58.920
What?

01:12:59.000 --> 01:13:00.422
He's fine.

01:13:02.461 --> 01:13:04.509
Just scraped and bruised is all.

01:13:13.639 --> 01:13:14.640
Hey.

01:13:15.766 --> 01:13:16.767
You okay?

01:13:37.914 --> 01:13:39.916
I wanna move 'em back to the country.

01:13:45.880 --> 01:13:47.882
I don't care what they do to us.

01:13:52.637 --> 01:13:54.514
I won't raise my family here.

01:15:02.707 --> 01:15:05.381
All right. Y'all get loaded up now.
Come on.

01:15:05.584 --> 01:15:06.672
Thank you, Al.

01:15:06.752 --> 01:15:07.924
Thank you, Don.

01:15:10.006 --> 01:15:11.177
Thank you, Miss Laura.

01:15:11.257 --> 01:15:12.383
Hmm.

01:15:16.262 --> 01:15:17.514
You just go on.

01:15:31.819 --> 01:15:33.446
I'll see you tonight.

01:15:35.448 --> 01:15:38.167
- You all be good.
- Okay, Daddy.

01:16:41.806 --> 01:16:42.807
Hey.

01:17:06.914 --> 01:17:08.666
Daddy!

01:17:27.226 --> 01:17:29.274
My cousin has a house he might rent out.

01:17:29.562 --> 01:17:32.065
But I thought Jim's brother
said it was fine here.

01:17:33.065 --> 01:17:36.069
I don't trust them. Too many people.

01:17:39.738 --> 01:17:40.739
Where is it?

01:17:41.073 --> 01:17:42.416
King and Queen County.

01:17:42.950 --> 01:17:44.577
Just a farmhouse up there.

01:17:45.244 --> 01:17:47.372
I figure it gets you out the county,
but keeps you close.

01:17:47.997 --> 01:17:49.123
You'll be on your own out there.

01:17:49.206 --> 01:17:50.833
It don't have no phone or nothing,

01:17:50.916 --> 01:17:53.510
but no one's gonna find you
unless they know to look.

01:17:54.420 --> 01:17:56.218
I can get word to you when you need it.

01:17:57.298 --> 01:17:58.891
How much you think he'd want for it?

01:17:59.884 --> 01:18:01.056
Ah, he'll be fair.

01:18:59.652 --> 01:19:00.824
Hey, look.

01:19:08.911 --> 01:19:10.163
Peggy!

01:19:55.332 --> 01:19:56.333
Hey.

01:19:57.751 --> 01:19:59.465
I'll try and get home before dark.

01:19:59.545 --> 01:20:00.546
Mmm-hmm.

01:20:02.339 --> 01:20:03.465
We'll be fine.

01:20:13.809 --> 01:20:17.154
"We haven't heard anything from you
for so long we had given up hope."

01:20:26.572 --> 01:20:30.702
Martha, call Chet Antieau's office at
Georgetown Law and try to set a meeting.

01:20:30.784 --> 01:20:32.127
Yes, Mr. Cohen.

01:20:35.497 --> 01:20:36.794
Come in.

01:20:37.374 --> 01:20:39.546
I'd never seen anything like it, you know.

01:20:39.626 --> 01:20:40.839
Excuse me.

01:20:40.919 --> 01:20:43.923
No matter how many times I get down south,
there's always something that surprises me.

01:20:45.299 --> 01:20:47.597
Oh, yes. Please bring him back.

01:20:47.926 --> 01:20:49.014
This is good timing.

01:20:49.094 --> 01:20:51.058
I want you to meet
a former student of mine.

01:20:51.138 --> 01:20:53.186
He called about a case
you may find interesting.

01:20:54.933 --> 01:20:56.355
Yeah, sure. What's it about?

01:20:56.435 --> 01:21:00.234
Well, we only spoke briefly
on the phone, but, in essence...

01:21:00.773 --> 01:21:02.150
Ah...

01:21:02.232 --> 01:21:03.779
Hello, Professor, thanks for seeing me.

01:21:03.859 --> 01:21:05.736
My pleasure.
You've come at a good time, Bernie.

01:21:05.944 --> 01:21:07.032
This is Phil Hirschkop.

01:21:07.112 --> 01:21:08.955
He's a brilliant civil rights lawyer.

01:21:10.783 --> 01:21:11.870
Nice to meet you.

01:21:11.950 --> 01:21:13.042
So...

01:21:13.619 --> 01:21:15.041
What's the problem?

01:21:15.662 --> 01:21:16.834
Well, I'm a bit stumped.

01:21:17.790 --> 01:21:21.002
The ACLU referred me to this case
concerning an interracial couple

01:21:21.085 --> 01:21:22.803
that was married in D.C.

01:21:23.295 --> 01:21:25.843
They were arrested for
living together in Virginia,

01:21:25.923 --> 01:21:27.550
and the judge suspended their sentence

01:21:27.633 --> 01:21:30.261
under order that they
leave the state for 25 years.

01:21:31.178 --> 01:21:34.143
I filed a motion to vacate the
judgment with Judge Bazile,

01:21:34.223 --> 01:21:37.062
the original trial judge
in Caroline County,

01:21:37.142 --> 01:21:38.314
but he's stonewalling me.

01:21:39.311 --> 01:21:43.566
Of course, the ACLU sees this,
and I agree, as a potential contender

01:21:43.649 --> 01:21:46.448
to repeal the anti-miscegenation
laws nationwide.

01:21:47.986 --> 01:21:50.580
I just need to get the
ball rolling, as it were.

01:21:55.244 --> 01:21:57.747
It's a very delicate
situation because by appealing,

01:21:57.830 --> 01:22:00.504
you open up the possibility of
sending them both to prison.

01:22:01.583 --> 01:22:05.090
I think regardless, file the 1983
motion explaining your complaint.

01:22:05.170 --> 01:22:08.594
It'll force Bazile's hand and get you
in front of a federal three-judge panel.

01:22:08.674 --> 01:22:09.762
All right.

01:22:09.842 --> 01:22:11.305
Look, I got to catch a plane
to New York tonight,

01:22:11.385 --> 01:22:13.387
but I'll work up a draft
and I'll find you on Monday?

01:22:13.887 --> 01:22:16.602
Great. That's just great. Thank you.

01:22:16.682 --> 01:22:19.772
Yeah. And, Bernie,
if you don't mind me asking,

01:22:19.852 --> 01:22:22.403
how much experience do you have
with constitutional law?

01:22:22.813 --> 01:22:24.030
Some.

01:22:28.026 --> 01:22:29.494
Very little.

01:22:30.863 --> 01:22:34.162
You realize this case could alter
the constitution of the United States?

01:22:35.868 --> 01:22:36.869
I do.

01:22:39.872 --> 01:22:41.044
I'll call you on Monday.

01:22:43.041 --> 01:22:45.214
One, two, three!

01:22:47.296 --> 01:22:48.548
I'm a good dog!

01:22:55.345 --> 01:22:56.642
I can never get mine to rise.

01:22:56.722 --> 01:22:59.396
It's not you. It's the humidity.

01:23:00.184 --> 01:23:01.902
Just thick.

01:23:02.060 --> 01:23:03.812
Come look, Meme. Come look.

01:23:03.896 --> 01:23:05.944
- Peggy.
- She's fine.

01:23:06.273 --> 01:23:08.116
What you want from your Meme?

01:23:08.400 --> 01:23:10.573
Lilly won't share her tea.

01:23:12.571 --> 01:23:14.073
She must be upset.

01:23:15.491 --> 01:23:16.743
Well, she wants to sit with us out here.

01:23:36.345 --> 01:23:38.188
Momma, get Peggy inside!

01:23:40.432 --> 01:23:41.604
Bean!

01:23:46.438 --> 01:23:47.940
Hey. What is it?

01:23:48.899 --> 01:23:50.367
Well, I got a message for you.

01:23:51.777 --> 01:23:52.990
What?

01:23:53.070 --> 01:23:55.789
Well, that lawyer called.
Said he wanna meet with y'all.

01:23:58.659 --> 01:24:00.878
Sidney! Donald!

01:24:02.412 --> 01:24:05.757
Raymond, why you
driving so fast like that?

01:24:06.792 --> 01:24:08.630
What you mean? I always drive like that.

01:24:14.675 --> 01:24:15.676
- What?
- Richard.

01:24:18.345 --> 01:24:20.643
- What is it?
- It's okay.

01:24:23.100 --> 01:24:26.104
"Almighty God created
the races white, black,

01:24:26.186 --> 01:24:30.569
"yellow, Malay, and red, and he
placed them on separate continents.

01:24:30.649 --> 01:24:32.902
"And but for the interference
with his arrangement

01:24:32.985 --> 01:24:35.113
"there would be no cause
for such marriages.

01:24:36.321 --> 01:24:37.868
"The fact that he separated the races

01:24:37.948 --> 01:24:40.417
"shows that he did not intend
for the races to mix."

01:24:42.661 --> 01:24:47.003
I know it sounds strange,
but this is really wonderful.

01:24:47.708 --> 01:24:50.923
By issuing this ruling, Judge Bazile
has really given us a road map

01:24:51.003 --> 01:24:52.676
right to the Supreme Court.

01:24:54.840 --> 01:24:56.558
I'm sorry, I'm confused.

01:24:57.593 --> 01:24:59.595
He ruled against us again.

01:25:00.429 --> 01:25:03.727
That's right, but now we're allowed
to appeal that ruling to the state.

01:25:03.807 --> 01:25:07.944
From there, if the state rules against you,
we'll have a chance at the Supreme Court.

01:25:11.315 --> 01:25:12.908
That sounds wonderful.

01:25:13.525 --> 01:25:16.278
I have one little piece of housekeeping.

01:25:16.361 --> 01:25:19.952
LIFE magazine contacted us about
sending a photographer out to you all.

01:25:20.032 --> 01:25:23.872
Keeping the possibility of
the Supreme Court in mind,

01:25:23.952 --> 01:25:28.377
I think it's a fair idea that we
raise the profile of your case,

01:25:28.457 --> 01:25:32.841
but I, of course, want to make sure
that you are all comfortable with that.

01:25:39.426 --> 01:25:40.723
It'll be fine.

01:25:58.028 --> 01:25:59.280
Hello!

01:26:07.746 --> 01:26:09.589
Grey Villet, LIFE magazine. Pleasure.

01:26:11.541 --> 01:26:12.918
What you got there, a small block?

01:26:13.960 --> 01:26:15.007
Yeah. Yeah.

01:26:15.087 --> 01:26:16.259
What's the trouble?

01:26:17.089 --> 01:26:18.427
Carburetors.

01:26:18.507 --> 01:26:19.508
Oh.

01:26:20.926 --> 01:26:23.054
Then you're a better mechanic than me.

01:26:24.096 --> 01:26:26.440
If you rejet them,
it goes faster, though, right?

01:26:27.724 --> 01:26:29.567
I'm sure you already know that.

01:26:29.685 --> 01:26:31.858
Is your wife inside?

01:26:32.270 --> 01:26:33.271
Uh-huh.

01:26:40.612 --> 01:26:42.330
Oh. Hello.

01:26:43.573 --> 01:26:46.076
Grey Villet. LIFE magazine.

01:26:46.910 --> 01:26:47.911
May I?

01:26:47.994 --> 01:26:49.541
Of course. Come in.

01:26:51.623 --> 01:26:53.420
Oh. Something smells good in there.

01:26:54.668 --> 01:26:57.758
So, I can't go back without
a photo. No photo, no job.

01:26:57.838 --> 01:27:00.717
And this is LIFE magazine and
the pigeon guy isn't around.

01:27:00.799 --> 01:27:02.551
- Pigeon guy?
- Pigeon guy?

01:27:02.634 --> 01:27:03.760
That's right.

01:27:03.844 --> 01:27:06.393
Looking up at this office
building and it hits me.

01:27:07.472 --> 01:27:10.601
Right. I go 55 stories up

01:27:11.059 --> 01:27:13.979
and I talk some office girls
into letting me look out the window.

01:27:14.354 --> 01:27:16.607
Before they could do anything,
I throw open the window,

01:27:16.690 --> 01:27:18.403
sit on the ledge and dangle my feet out.

01:27:19.609 --> 01:27:22.449
They start screaming,
but I got this great shot

01:27:22.529 --> 01:27:25.533
of my feet flying over
42nd and 5th Avenue.

01:27:26.450 --> 01:27:27.793
Yeah. So what happened?

01:27:28.660 --> 01:27:30.913
Security threw me out head first.

01:27:31.455 --> 01:27:33.878
But, LIFE magazine hired me the next day.

01:27:35.584 --> 01:27:37.632
That's a story, all right.

01:27:37.753 --> 01:27:40.802
Yeah, that's a story, all right.

01:27:45.343 --> 01:27:47.471
You go to the Virginia
State Court next, right?

01:27:47.554 --> 01:27:48.771
Yes.

01:27:50.849 --> 01:27:52.066
You nervous?

01:27:53.018 --> 01:27:54.064
I suppose.

01:27:54.144 --> 01:27:55.357
Hmm.

01:27:55.437 --> 01:27:57.485
The lawyers told us not to expect much.

01:27:58.690 --> 01:28:00.192
You think you'll lose?

01:28:01.234 --> 01:28:02.611
Well, yes.

01:28:04.404 --> 01:28:05.951
But I think it's all right.

01:28:08.158 --> 01:28:10.877
We may lose the small battles,
but win the big war.

01:28:26.218 --> 01:28:27.764
- ...coleslaw.
- Yeah.

01:28:27.844 --> 01:28:29.846
And here's the surprise.

01:28:29.971 --> 01:28:32.019
Some of my new homemade pickles.

01:28:34.810 --> 01:28:37.274
That certainly is a wonderful surprise.

01:28:37.354 --> 01:28:41.069
Look at that, Barney, Aunt Bee's brought
us some of her homemade pickles.

01:28:41.149 --> 01:28:43.243
I see. Sure is wonderful.

01:28:43.610 --> 01:28:45.237
You really shouldn't have, Aunt Bee.

01:28:45.320 --> 01:28:46.992
That's right, Aunt Bee.

01:28:47.072 --> 01:28:50.576
You go to way yonder too
much trouble to please us.

01:28:50.659 --> 01:28:52.787
It's no trouble at all.

01:28:52.869 --> 01:28:55.088
There's plenty. I made eight quarts.

01:28:55.247 --> 01:28:56.835
Eight quarts?

01:28:56.915 --> 01:29:00.169
Aunt Bee made eight quarts. Eight quarts.

01:29:00.335 --> 01:29:02.424
You can have some every day.

01:29:04.214 --> 01:29:06.386
Well, I had an awful big breakfast.

01:29:06.466 --> 01:29:09.014
I just stuffed myself something fierce.

01:29:09.094 --> 01:29:10.766
Have some pickles.

01:29:10.846 --> 01:29:11.972
Here you are.

01:29:14.057 --> 01:29:16.059
And here you are.

01:29:25.110 --> 01:29:26.698
Mr. Loving. Mr. Loving.

01:29:26.778 --> 01:29:28.576
They just wanna ask you a few questions.

01:29:31.491 --> 01:29:33.289
Uh... All right.

01:29:37.873 --> 01:29:39.875
Mrs. Loving, you rolling?

01:29:40.375 --> 01:29:43.673
Mrs. Loving, the Virginia Supreme Court
just ruled against you.

01:29:43.753 --> 01:29:46.006
How do you feel about
what happened here today?

01:29:46.923 --> 01:29:48.391
Well, I feel hopeful.

01:29:48.967 --> 01:29:50.219
I'm hopeful.

01:29:51.052 --> 01:29:52.554
And where will you go now?

01:29:54.639 --> 01:29:56.607
Well, I guess we'll go back to Washington.

01:29:56.766 --> 01:29:58.814
You'll go back to Washington?

01:29:58.894 --> 01:30:02.647
Mr. Loving, do you have anything to say
about what went on in the court today?

01:30:03.064 --> 01:30:04.816
No. I don't have anything to say.

01:30:05.150 --> 01:30:07.118
Okay. Thank you, folks, very much.

01:30:07.402 --> 01:30:08.654
Did you get that?

01:30:08.737 --> 01:30:10.990
- I think so.
- Okay, cut, Tommy.

01:30:13.658 --> 01:30:14.830
Mr. and Mrs. Loving?

01:30:18.496 --> 01:30:21.878
We wanted you to know that, with all
this travel back and forth from Virginia,

01:30:21.958 --> 01:30:24.086
you have my number
and if anybody arrests you,

01:30:24.169 --> 01:30:26.137
you have them get in touch with us.

01:30:26.838 --> 01:30:29.261
We're not gonna let you spend
one minute longer in jail

01:30:29.341 --> 01:30:32.185
than it takes us to get down
there to get you out, okay?

01:30:32.469 --> 01:30:33.932
Okay.

01:30:34.012 --> 01:30:35.684
Good luck to you.

01:30:35.764 --> 01:30:36.936
You did a good job today.

01:30:37.974 --> 01:30:39.896
Well, I sure appreciate
what y'all are doing.

01:30:39.976 --> 01:30:41.102
Okay.

01:30:41.186 --> 01:30:42.232
Well, we'll see you soon.

01:30:42.312 --> 01:30:43.313
Bye.

01:30:46.691 --> 01:30:48.238
Thank you, gentlemen.

01:30:49.694 --> 01:30:52.284
You know they aren't
going back to Washington.

01:30:52.364 --> 01:30:55.496
And there's no guarantee we can
get them out if they get arrested again.

01:30:56.826 --> 01:30:57.998
Mmm-hmm.

01:33:29.854 --> 01:33:30.855
Sidney!

01:33:32.982 --> 01:33:34.029
Sidney!

01:33:36.694 --> 01:33:38.412
I want you to go next
door to the neighbor.

01:33:38.988 --> 01:33:40.410
You gonna ask him to use the telephone

01:33:40.490 --> 01:33:43.369
and you gonna call Raymond
and ask him to bring his gun, okay?

01:33:43.451 --> 01:33:45.670
Go. Go on now.
Run through the woods. Go on.

01:33:51.501 --> 01:33:52.753
Everything okay?

01:33:54.212 --> 01:33:55.338
It's fine.

01:33:56.881 --> 01:33:58.007
Richard?

01:33:58.091 --> 01:33:59.308
Go on inside.

01:34:36.421 --> 01:34:38.765
That truck may have
just been going fishing.

01:34:43.386 --> 01:34:44.979
Could be.

01:34:46.723 --> 01:34:49.272
You ever hear from anyone
at your work about it?

01:34:52.979 --> 01:34:54.606
Not to my face.

01:35:02.739 --> 01:35:07.952
Well, I'll tell you this, Rich,
nobody gonna tell you what you can't do.

01:35:21.382 --> 01:35:22.804
You're all set.

01:35:23.968 --> 01:35:24.969
Thank you.

01:35:26.137 --> 01:35:27.810
Who we gonna call, Momma?

01:35:27.972 --> 01:35:29.849
I don't want you calling anybody.

01:35:31.392 --> 01:35:32.393
How did that go?

01:35:32.560 --> 01:35:34.153
Doctor said she'll be fine.

01:35:34.312 --> 01:35:35.529
Just put her on aspirin.

01:35:36.773 --> 01:35:37.774
Who was that?

01:35:38.358 --> 01:35:39.735
Telephone man.

01:35:40.485 --> 01:35:42.078
Richard had him install a phone.

01:35:43.321 --> 01:35:44.538
Momma, you feel okay?

01:35:44.656 --> 01:35:45.657
Yes.

01:35:45.740 --> 01:35:47.787
- You got some tea I can drink?
- Mmm-hmm.

01:35:47.867 --> 01:35:48.868
All right.

01:36:11.516 --> 01:36:14.861
Testing, testing. Testing.

01:36:17.730 --> 01:36:20.028
What do you think you would do if you...

01:36:20.108 --> 01:36:21.360
If you lose the case?

01:36:23.778 --> 01:36:25.030
Well...

01:36:26.322 --> 01:36:30.543
If we lose, then we would have
to go back to Washington.

01:36:31.577 --> 01:36:34.334
And how does that make you feel
having to go back to Washington?

01:36:34.414 --> 01:36:36.007
Mildred?

01:36:40.503 --> 01:36:41.504
Come here.

01:36:47.427 --> 01:36:48.553
- Excuse me.
- Yeah.

01:37:02.317 --> 01:37:03.785
I don't want those people here.

01:37:04.610 --> 01:37:06.078
I'm done with all these cameras!

01:37:07.113 --> 01:37:08.535
Well, I think it's important.

01:37:11.075 --> 01:37:13.077
These people want to help us, Richard.

01:37:38.728 --> 01:37:42.235
Well, actually, although I'm sure
the publicity isn't very pleasant,

01:37:43.024 --> 01:37:46.532
if it works out for you, it will work out
for a lot of other people, too.

01:37:47.111 --> 01:37:48.112
Yes.

01:37:49.322 --> 01:37:50.323
I hope so.

01:37:51.908 --> 01:37:53.496
It's the principle.

01:37:53.576 --> 01:37:55.544
It's the law. I don't think it's right.

01:37:56.579 --> 01:38:01.509
And if... If we do win,
we will be helping a lot of people.

01:38:02.502 --> 01:38:03.754
Mmm-hmm.

01:38:05.088 --> 01:38:08.012
And I knew... I know we have some enemies,

01:38:08.216 --> 01:38:09.809
but we have some friends, too.

01:38:11.803 --> 01:38:15.355
So it really don't make a difference
about my enemies.

01:38:34.492 --> 01:38:35.994
Push in hard on that one.

01:38:36.077 --> 01:38:37.415
You go straight down the way, okay?

01:38:37.495 --> 01:38:39.042
I got it. I got it. Don't worry about it.

01:38:39.122 --> 01:38:40.248
- Hey. Good ride.
- All right.

01:38:40.331 --> 01:38:42.003
Make sure you get it
into second as quick as you can.

01:38:42.083 --> 01:38:43.335
- You got it.
- All right.

01:38:57.849 --> 01:38:59.312
Car looks good.

01:38:59.392 --> 01:39:00.769
Yeah, it's running all right.

01:39:04.188 --> 01:39:06.316
You see him driving today.

01:39:06.399 --> 01:39:08.868
It was like he was sitting
in the back seat.

01:39:16.951 --> 01:39:20.124
Oh, man. I miss you, Rich.

01:39:20.204 --> 01:39:21.918
Hell, I can say it.

01:39:21.998 --> 01:39:23.295
Hey, Percy, don't you miss Rich?

01:39:23.624 --> 01:39:24.716
Yeah.

01:39:26.169 --> 01:39:27.796
I miss you too, Virgil.

01:39:30.423 --> 01:39:33.142
Man. So, what's all this you got going?

01:39:34.135 --> 01:39:35.853
- All what?
- What you got.

01:39:36.262 --> 01:39:38.356
You just went made it hard now.

01:39:38.890 --> 01:39:42.568
No, no. You think I'm crazy,
but you know what hard is now, don't you?

01:39:43.686 --> 01:39:44.687
Yeah.

01:39:45.646 --> 01:39:47.068
Richard, you are white.

01:39:49.400 --> 01:39:51.869
Now, you may think you're like
a black man, but you're white.

01:39:52.570 --> 01:39:53.991
You hang around all these black folks,

01:39:54.071 --> 01:39:56.073
but when you go to work,
you're still white.

01:39:57.241 --> 01:39:58.413
But not now.

01:39:59.285 --> 01:40:01.413
Now you know what it feels
like now, don't you?

01:40:03.498 --> 01:40:05.421
You're black now, ain't you?

01:40:06.083 --> 01:40:08.256
- You're a damn fool.
- All right, come on now.

01:40:08.920 --> 01:40:10.467
No, he needs to hear it.

01:40:11.464 --> 01:40:13.887
Look, every nigga in here
wish they were you, Rich,

01:40:14.300 --> 01:40:16.018
and you ain't got sense enough for it.

01:40:16.427 --> 01:40:18.850
You got a fix. I ain't got no fix.

01:40:19.764 --> 01:40:21.477
So yours is easy.

01:40:21.557 --> 01:40:23.025
All you gotta do is divorce her.

01:40:24.227 --> 01:40:25.523
Divorce her?

01:40:25.603 --> 01:40:27.355
All you gotta do.

01:40:30.942 --> 01:40:32.488
- Yeah.
- Yeah. Really.

01:40:34.403 --> 01:40:35.996
- I'm gonna divorce her.
- That it.

01:40:37.782 --> 01:40:39.534
That's all you gotta do, right?

01:40:39.617 --> 01:40:41.210
That's all you gotta do.

01:40:47.458 --> 01:40:48.880
Apologize now, Virgil.

01:41:47.476 --> 01:41:48.693
Come to bed, Richard.

01:41:51.814 --> 01:41:53.282
We've been

01:41:54.734 --> 01:41:56.953
talking to lawyers for

01:41:59.363 --> 01:42:01.036
near 10 years now.

01:42:11.375 --> 01:42:12.422
Let's go to bed.

01:42:17.757 --> 01:42:19.350
I can take care of you.

01:42:23.346 --> 01:42:24.393
I know that.

01:42:34.732 --> 01:42:36.325
I can take care of you.

01:42:44.950 --> 01:42:45.997
I know.

01:42:49.914 --> 01:42:52.838
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

01:42:53.626 --> 01:42:54.627
It's okay.

01:43:54.603 --> 01:43:55.980
It's very good.

01:43:58.941 --> 01:44:00.909
Well, I have some really terrific news.

01:44:01.694 --> 01:44:03.783
The Supreme Court has agreed
to hear our case.

01:44:05.072 --> 01:44:08.201
Now, of course, the state
of Virginia will mount their defense,

01:44:08.701 --> 01:44:10.915
but we are feeling very good
about our chances here.

01:44:10.995 --> 01:44:13.623
You've got the full weight
of the ACLU behind this.

01:44:15.958 --> 01:44:17.505
- It's a miracle.
- Hmm.

01:44:20.004 --> 01:44:21.347
What's their defense?

01:44:22.798 --> 01:44:23.845
I'm sorry?

01:44:24.008 --> 01:44:25.351
Virginia.

01:44:27.011 --> 01:44:29.685
How are they gonna defend
what they done to us?

01:44:31.265 --> 01:44:33.142
I guess we won't know until the hearing,

01:44:33.225 --> 01:44:35.564
but it's likely that they'll use

01:44:35.644 --> 01:44:38.193
a defense similar to something
they've used before.

01:44:39.815 --> 01:44:41.112
What's that?

01:44:48.157 --> 01:44:49.204
It's your kids.

01:44:53.537 --> 01:44:54.584
Our kids?

01:44:59.293 --> 01:45:02.297
The state of Virginia
will argue that it is unfair

01:45:02.379 --> 01:45:04.973
to bring children
of mixed race into the world.

01:45:09.386 --> 01:45:11.559
They believe the children are bastards.

01:45:23.609 --> 01:45:25.656
Now, as the defendants in this trial,

01:45:25.736 --> 01:45:28.330
you are allowed to come
and hear the arguments.

01:45:32.409 --> 01:45:35.003
No. We don't need to do that.

01:45:37.039 --> 01:45:40.838
It's a tremendous honor to sit with
the Supreme Court. Very few people...

01:45:40.918 --> 01:45:42.090
No.

01:45:45.506 --> 01:45:46.598
That's fine.

01:45:48.843 --> 01:45:49.890
Excuse me.

01:46:03.274 --> 01:46:04.321
Mildred?

01:46:09.613 --> 01:46:11.536
I wouldn't go without him.

01:46:36.974 --> 01:46:40.353
You know, Richard, it's, of course,
up to you not to attend but,

01:46:41.979 --> 01:46:46.701
you should know, the Supreme Court
only hears one out of every 400 cases.

01:46:47.484 --> 01:46:48.531
It's historic.

01:46:55.826 --> 01:46:56.998
Thank you, Mr. Cohen.

01:46:58.996 --> 01:47:01.715
Well. Is there anything
you'd like me to say to them?

01:47:03.834 --> 01:47:07.464
And by "them" I mean the Supreme
Court justices of the United States?

01:47:16.013 --> 01:47:17.060
Yeah.

01:47:22.436 --> 01:47:23.483
You can tell the judge...

01:47:27.274 --> 01:47:29.197
Tell the judge I love my wife.

01:48:10.401 --> 01:48:12.904
You okay to park? Thanks, Martha.

01:48:20.577 --> 01:48:22.329
Number 395.

01:48:24.081 --> 01:48:28.336
Richard Perry Loving et al, Appellants,

01:48:29.670 --> 01:48:31.297
v. Virginia.

01:48:38.637 --> 01:48:40.059
Mr. Hirschkop.

01:48:50.983 --> 01:48:53.907
Mr. Chief Justice, Associate Justices,
may it please the court?

01:48:57.781 --> 01:49:03.245
You have before you today
what we consider the most odious

01:49:03.328 --> 01:49:05.918
of the segregation laws
and the slavery laws,

01:49:05.998 --> 01:49:09.127
and our view of this law,
and we hope to clearly show,

01:49:10.961 --> 01:49:12.713
is that this is a slavery law.

01:49:15.883 --> 01:49:19.513
We ask that the Court consider
the full spectrum of these laws

01:49:19.595 --> 01:49:20.891
and not just the criminality,

01:49:20.971 --> 01:49:25.067
because it's more than criminality
that's at point here.

01:49:26.477 --> 01:49:28.024
It's the right to inherit land,

01:49:29.688 --> 01:49:31.440
the legitimacy of children,

01:49:32.483 --> 01:49:33.985
and many, many rights.

01:49:36.820 --> 01:49:37.912
Mr. Cohen.

01:49:46.538 --> 01:49:48.381
Mr. Chief Justice,
may it please the court?

01:49:50.793 --> 01:49:55.097
What is the danger to the state
of Virginia of interracial marriage?

01:50:01.178 --> 01:50:06.229
What is the state of danger
to the people of interracial marriage?

